resource.chars: When Fauvel had chattered on hypocritically,
Fortune, to whom are revealed
The thoughts of men and women,
She, who above all women
Has the faculty, in all instances,
Quickly finds a quarrel with Fauvel
For begging her love in this way:
â€œI had told you, long before,
That your desire to have me as your wife
Was without cause; if you have brayed
Enough, let me speak in reply:
You cannot choose the best!
I am Fortune the feared,
The very powerful, the renowned,
The very lofty, noble and well bred,
And I am the daughter of the very powerful king,
In that I am, through my excellence,
A property of his essence,
With my sister who is so beautiful
That Reason calls her Wisdom.
And we are, it is true,
Of a divine nature,
So that we are truly
Without ending or beginning.
But the intellectual gaze,
Not the real one, may God keep me,
Gives to my sister, in a very subtle way,
A small advantage of age.
But one cannot exist without the other.
We are seated on the right
Of the all powerful, eternal king,
The lofty, merciful king of the sky,
In his admirable royalty.
The angels, in front of our beauty,
As well as the saints who arrive in the sky
Marvel at it and dwell there.
They cannot have their fill
Of looking at us and our beings.
The more they look at us, the more they contemplate us,
And they do not desire anything except to gaze at us.
Fauvel, you are crazy and you were crazy
When you thought and believed
That I was like a woman
And that you had to marry me!
You were full of a great madness
When you thought of such a high marriage!
You wanted to lift your comb too high,
You who want to marry a royal daughter!
You are badly deceived,
You who invested yourself in this way!
If you had considered well
Where you are, where you come from, and what you were,
You would never have undertaken
Elevating yourself in worth,
For you are nothing but excrement and filth,
An animal of evil nature,
Who exerts great effort in nourishing itself.
And soon you will be rotting flesh!
You were conceived horribly
And nourished in the womb in filth
From the most base material
That Nature was ever able to make.
And when you were inside the womb,
You were enveloped in filthy tissues.
Your chamber was a tiny space.
You were born into dishonor and sadness,
And your mother suffered great pain from it.
And quickly you began to bray.
It is a very bitter birth
Which comes in such great misery!
And now pride has entrapped you
So that you have forgotten all of this.
Fauvel, listen well, as is fitting
For through you I mean truly
The evilness of man and woman
Who condemns his soul for the sake of his body,
And who, for the deceitful world,
Loses God and all enduring good.
Consider that even if one combs and rubs you,
You are nothing but a sack full of shit.
But pride has so overcome you
That you do not direct your attention towards anything good.
It does not interest you except to exert yourself
In having worldly wealth,
And you will never be tired of this,
Even though you have plenty.
And you are a great master in this world
And you make everyone graze with you.
You are guided only by your desire.
You first began a long time ago
To be a lord in the world;
But you are greater today
Than you ever were before.
Your cousins are spread everywhere,
And your servants and your followers.
And I suffer that you lead this kind of life
Because I know the secret of God
Who, through his reasonable will,
Wants that, at the end of this world,
There be an abundance of wars, evil and sin
Since everyone exerts so much effort
To achieve worldly excellence,
To serving and loving the world.
This is why God plants great bitterness,
So that he be able to separate
Those who want to satiate themselves too much.
And for this reason, I will tell you, without interruption,
Along with this, another reason
Why evil exists and calamities abound
In such great number at the end of the world,
Even if he through whom evil arrives
Will receive the malediction of God.
The author of Six Principles says
And Reason does not contradict it,
That the world has the name Macrocosm
And man is Microcosm.
And this signifies and means
That there is a bigger world and a lesser one
And the one resembles the other.
And it is in this way, as it seems to me,
That man has four qualities
Which have conflict between them,
For one is contrary to the other.
There is only war in their company.
